#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:2
#: 6fa1c2175ab645f3899651f3de6eca47
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:4
#: 41bed1d5166b4ae48d38828757f3db03
msgid ""
"TensorMesh runs on Linux, macOS, and Windows. The only hard requirements "
"are **Python ≥ 3.10** and **PyTorch ≥ 2.0**; everything else (NumPy, "
"SciPy, meshio, ``torch-sla``, ...) is pulled in automatically by ``pip``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:8
#: 126f3ffa1e744aaaa2fb8d161ca6e2a1
msgid ""
"If you plan to use the GPU backend, install a CUDA-enabled PyTorch build "
"*before* installing TensorMesh — follow the official `PyTorch "
"installation selector <https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/>`_ for "
"the right command on your platform / CUDA version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:15
#: ac1e2fa8b7cb4b73bd1b4ee3818b85dd
msgid "Install via PyPI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:17
#: 6a11f69a800545ecad0f0d81c2b3bce0
msgid "The recommended way to install TensorMesh is from PyPI:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:24
#: 50f7b6853ad44b378184535c8ecbf3bc
msgid ""
"Use the second form if you have an NVIDIA GPU and want the CUDA sparse-"
"solver backends — the ``[gpu]`` extra pulls in both CuPy and cuDSS "
"through ``torch-sla``. The quotes are needed because ``[...]`` is a shell"
" glob character; see `Sparse solvers and GPU acceleration`_ for the per-"
"backend breakdown if you only want one of CuPy or cuDSS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:30
#: 93e0a8630f6248408fe1340551e6a61e
msgid ""
"Either form pulls in all required dependencies, including `torch-sla "
"<https://www.torchsla.com/>`_, the differentiable sparse linear algebra "
"library that powers TensorMesh's solvers. The base ``pip install tensor-"
"mesh`` installs only the **CPU** sparse stack (SciPy / Eigen / native "
"PyTorch); see `Sparse solvers and GPU acceleration`_ below for the full "
"extras matrix (``[cupy]`` / ``[cudss]`` / ``[gpu]``) and how to verify "
"which backends are usable on your machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:40
#: be9c48347bb84550a79b43a4051e8d4b
msgid "Install from source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:42
#: f610c5b34111442f9b3c92c220b50193
msgid ""
"For development work, or to get the latest unreleased changes, clone the "
"repository and install in editable mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:51
#: c0fc83c38ee74799af52fb927d0a7cc5
msgid ""
"The ``-e`` (editable) flag means edits to the source tree are picked up "
"without reinstalling. To install with the test dependencies as well:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:60
#: f17982ef981c4f378973aa8e25d6513f
msgid "Sparse solvers and GPU acceleration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:62
#: 632da170d9ab4705aebabe5fd0362bf6
msgid ""
"The sparse linear-algebra layer that powers TensorMesh's solvers lives in"
" a standalone library, `torch-sla <https://www.torchsla.com/>`_, so that "
"it can evolve independently and serve other projects. ``torch-sla`` is a "
"**hard, import-time** dependency — :mod:`tensormesh.sparse` will not "
"import without it — and is the canonical entry point for both CPU and GPU"
" sparse solves. All current and future solver work lands in ``torch-sla``"
" first; we recommend keeping it up to date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/installation.rst:70
#: c2fd3bbd54f147c29afa3e42b7e1d0f2
msgid ""
"The base ``tensor-mesh`` wheel only pulls the **CPU** stack (SciPy / "
"Eigen / native PyTorch). To enable a GPU backend, install one of the "
"mirrored extras:"
